Register JSON-Home data for resources with parent

This patch adds support to register json-home data for resources
with parent.

Some resources gets resigtered along with parent resource
for example 'os-instance-action' with parent resource 'servers'.

JSON-Home data for such resources will be stored along with their parent
resource information. Means those resource relation will have parent resource.

json-home data for resources with parent will looks like-
{
    "http://docs.openstack.org/api/openstack-compute/2.1/rel/servers/os-instance-actions": {
      "href-template": "/v2.1/{project_id}/servers/{server_id}/os-instance-actions",
      "href-vars": {
        "project_id": "http://docs.openstack.org/api/openstack-compute/2.1/param/project_id",
        "server_id": "http://docs.openstack.org/api/openstack-compute/2.1/param/server_id"
      }
    },
    "http://docs.openstack.org/api/openstack-compute/2.1/rel/servers/os-instance-action": {
      "href-template": "/v2.1/{project_id}/servers/{server_id}/os-instance-actions/{action_id}",
      "href-vars": {
        "project_id": "http://docs.openstack.org/api/openstack-compute/2.1/param/project_id",
        "server_id": "http://docs.openstack.org/api/openstack-compute/2.1/param/server_id",
        "action_id": "http://docs.openstack.org/api/openstack-compute/2.1/param/action_id"
      }
    },
    [..]
}

Partially implements blueprint nova-api-json-home

Change-Id: I453ba0d345111d71728124ee82066f1e92359e9a

Support for registering JSON-Home data- show/delete/update

This patch adds support to register json-home data for resources
having show/delete/update methods.

json-home data for show/create/delete will looks like-

{
    "http://docs.openstack.org/api/openstack-compute/2.1/rel/server": {
      "href-template": "/v2.1/{project_id}/servers/{server_id}",
      "href-vars": {
        "project_id": "http://docs.openstack.org/api/openstack-compute/2.1/param/project_id"
        "server_id": "http://docs.openstack.org/api/openstack-compute/2.1/param/server_id"
      }
    },
    "http://docs.openstack.org/api/openstack-compute/2.1/rel/flavor": {
      "href-template": "/v2.1/{project_id}/flavors/flavor_id",
      "href-vars": {
        "project_id": "http://docs.openstack.org/api/openstack-compute/2.1/param/project_id"
        "flavor_id": "http://docs.openstack.org/api/openstack-compute/2.1/param/flavor_id"
      }
    },
    [..]
}

Resources with singular names like 'os-simple-tenant-usage' and has show/update/delete
methods which expect some param will be having relation name by appending 'with_param'
in resource name like below-

{
    'http://docs.openstack.org/api/openstack-compute/2.1/rel/'
    'os-simple-tenant-usage': {
        'href-template': '/v2.1/{project_id}/os-simple-tenant-usage',
        'href-vars': {
            'project_id': 'http://docs.openstack.org/api/openstack-compute/'
                          '2.1/param/project_id'
        }
    },
   'http://docs.openstack.org/api/openstack-compute/2.1/rel/'
   'os-simple-tenant-usage_with_param': {
        'href-template': '/v2.1/{project_id}/os-simple-tenant-usage/'
                         '{tenant_id}',
        'href-vars': {
            'project_id': 'http://docs.openstack.org/api/openstack-compute/'
                          '2.1/param/project_id',
            'tenant_id': 'http://docs.openstack.org/api/openstack-compute/'
                         '2.1/param/tenant_id'
        }
   }
}

